headline.canonical: Sky and Adobe launch 'The Edit' student challenge to improve digital literacy and champion equality and diversity

abstract.snippet: Sky and Adobe launch 'The Edit' student challenge in partnership with Kick It Out to improve digital literacy and champion equality and diversity among young people.
abstract.standFirst: The Edit, launched by Sky and Adobe, is a digital programme aimed at schools in low-income areas designed to improve the digital literacy of young people and inspire the next generation of British media talent by breaking down historical industry barriers to entry
abstract.leadParagraph: Sky and Adobe have launched 'The Edit' student challenge in partnership with Kick It Out to improve digital literacy and champion equality and diversity among young people across the country.

media.caption: Sky Sports' Johnny Nelson is an ambassador for The Edit programme
media.description: Johnny Nelson

headline.index: Kirk: NHL chance proves dreams can come true
headline.long: Liam Kirk: Great Britain forward says 'dreams can come true' after joining NHL's Arizona Coyotes
headline.mobile: Kirk: NHL chance proves dreams can come true
headline.canonical: Liam Kirk: Great Britain forward says 'dreams can come true' after joining NHL's Arizona Coyotes

abstract.snippet: Liam Kirk is "living proof" that British ice hockey players can make their dreams come true after signing a three-year entry level deal with the NHL's Arizona Coyotes.
abstract.standFirst: From Sheffield to Arizona via Peterborough, Ontario, Liam Kirk has taken another stride towards his goal of playing in the NHL; the 21-year-old tells Matt Ford how he hopes others will now follow in his footsteps and turn their dreams into reality
abstract.leadParagraph: Liam Kirk believes he is "living proof" that young British ice hockey players can make their dreams come true after signing a three-year entry level contract with the NHL's Arizona Coyotes.

media.description: AP - Liam Kirk of Britain celebrates a goal during the Ice Hockey World Championship group A match between the Britain and Denmark at the Olympic Sports Center in Riga, Latvia, Wednesday, May 26, 2021. (AP Photo/Roman Koksarov)
